The Federal Executive Council yesterday approved $6.7 billion for construction of the Ibadan-Kaduna rail. The Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, said this while briefing State House correspondents after the FEC meeting presided over by President Muhammadu Buhari. The minister said completion period of the project was three years. Also, the Minister of the Federal Capital Territory, Mohammed Musa Bello said the council awarded contract for the reconstruction of the Bill Clinton Drive Road for N1.9 billion. The minister put the completion period of the project at seven months. Bello said the council also awarded a supply of chemicals to FCT water companies for N273 million.